GOSPEL singer Bongi Matlhabane has just released amapiano gospel album Nwana Davida on digital music platforms, taking Mzansi by storm with hits Bambelelaand Hita Tshama. The born-again Christian serves as worship team leader in her village’s New Covenant Church. She realised her talent at the age of 11. Born and bred in Kumani Village outside Thulamahashe near Bushbuckridge in 1982, Bongi is also is the director of Tlhavula Boma. Bongi became known for her album Tiyisela  in 2007 and Trust In Him in 2009. In 2013, enrolling as a nursing student, she released her popular album I Thank You Lord featuring Uyanginakekela and Hi Hanya Mahala. She joined Go Explo Gospel group under Kenny Shibambu in Limpopo, gaining live experience. She has shared the stage with Joyous Celebration, Solly Mahlangu and Worship House at the Mapungubwe Music Festival in Limpopo. ALSO READ : NTENCANE TAKES FANS BY STORM In 2017, she was part of the Africa Love and Hope Music Festival featuring Bishop Benjamin Dube, Lebo Sekgobela and Neyi Zimu. In 2017 she bagged Sunrise Women’s Best Gospel Artist Award and a certificate and trophy as Best Female Artist during Bushbuckridge Golden Stars Awards in 2017 and 2019. In 2019, she also won Best Gospel Album Award in Tsonga for her album Tatana Wa Hina during the Gospel Music Awards in Giyani, as well as Best Gospel Song of the Year for Mapfula Ku Pfariwile at Xigma 2020. On 30 December, Bongi hosted a free music festival, Kumani: “Let’s Have Fun and Fun” in her village to give back and inspire youth. “The event was very successful,” she said.